Israel Stocks: Africa Israel Properties, Bioline, Elbit, Koor

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-05-18T08:37:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/israel-stocks-africa-israel-properties-bioline-elbit-koor.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index advanced for a
third day, increasing 0.7 percent to 1,298.08 at 11:08 a.m. in
Tel Aviv.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Africa Israel Properties Ltd. (AFPR IT) climbed the most in
almost a week, adding 1 percent to 43.50 shekels. The real-
estate developer said first-quarter net income increased to 19.2
million shekels ($5.4 million) from 14.7 million shekels a year
earlier.  Bioline RX Ltd. (BLRX)   rose 2.3 percent to 1.95 shekels,
headed for the biggest gain since April 4. The biopharmaceutical
development company said it received approval in Romania to
start a trial of its BL-1020 drug to treat schizophrenia.  Elbit Systems Ltd. (ESLT)   rose for a second day, adding
1.4 percent to 184.30 shekels. Israel’s biggest non-government
defense contractor won a $20 million maritime patrol aircraft
contract from an unidentified Asian country.  Koor Industries Ltd. (KOR)   dropped for the third time
this week, declining 1.2 percent to 74.46 shekels. The holding
company said first-quarter net income fell to 130.7 million
shekels from 207.4 million shekels a year earlier.  Nice Systems Ltd. (NICE)   gained for the second time in
three days, climbing 1.8 percent to 126.70 shekels. China’s
Tianjin Metro will install the maker of digital-recording
surveillance products’ system across 23 stations.  To contact the reporter on this story:  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in  Jerusalem  at 
 Slerner2@bloomberg.net . 